{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fa8712bc-d060-444a-81c2-9584ae13cf6e","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's what's happening and what else to watch for:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Tests lost history in Azure DevOps\n\nMSTest v4 changed the **default test ID format** to fully-qualified names. Azure DevOps sees these as entirely new tests. Fix by opting back in to the old ID scheme in your `.runsettings`:\n\n```xml\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <TestIdGenerationStrategy>Legacy</TestIdGenerationStrategy>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\n### 2. `TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]` throws\n\nIn v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is now a **class-level** context — it has no individual test associated with it, so `TestName` throws. This is by design because class init runs once, not per-test.\n\n**Fix** — remove the `TestName` access from `ClassInit`:\n\n```csharp\n[ClassInitialize]\npublic static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n{\n    // context.TestName is no longer available here in v4.\n    // Use context for class-level logging only.\n}\n```\n\nIf you need per-test setup, move that logic to `[TestInitialize]` where `TestContext.TestName` still works.\n\n### 3. Other key v4 changes to watch for\n\n| Area | Change |\n|---|---|\n| **`[DataRow]` type coercion** | Implicit numeric conversions (e.g., `int` → `long`) are stricter; mismatches may fail at compile time or runtime. |\n| **Parallel execution** | Now **enabled by default** at the method level. Add `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]` or disable if tests share state. |\n| **`Assert.AreEqual` on doubles** | Floating-point tolerance comparison semantics tightened. |\n| **`DeploymentItem`** | Deprecated in favor of build-time copy; may silently stop deploying files. |\n| **Timeout default** | Test timeouts are now enforced more strictly via `CooperativeCancellation`. |\n\nParallel execution being on by default is the most common source of \"tests that used to pass now flake\" after a v4 upgrade.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3f0d666c-35d1-4c32-a686-b81e1c707dd9","outputTokens":553},"id":"70dce7fa-b443-44b3-8950-7ff4b183bf1d","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:03:18.582Z","parentId":"ffe4fbec-5ec4-4eba-89cc-dff7062911ce"}
